        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 6:26PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 626 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Claude to 12 miles southeast of Washburn
to 6 miles north of Palo Duro Canyon. Movement was southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Claude and Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
